<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9237] DefaultSolrHighlighter.doHighlightingByFastVectorHighlighter can&apos;t be overidden</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9237</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;b&gt;6.1.0&lt;/b&gt; the &lt;b&gt;protected&lt;/b&gt; method DefaultSolrHighlighter.doHighlightingByFastVectorHighlighter passes in a &lt;b&gt;private&lt;/b&gt; class called FvhContainer which makes it very difficult to extend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have code that extends DefaultSolrHighlighter which I can&apos;t fix due to this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
Could you consider making FvhContainer  &quot;protected&quot; and use a constructor?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
